ce":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-11745/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-11745/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-11745/canvas/1/44714d72-5aa5-4677-8534-bfcc0968ded0","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2025-08-27T19:48:52.326Z","creator":"Olivia Flores","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This shot, as it pushes in on Philip Seymour Hoffman's Mattress Man, resembles several others featuring Barry throughout the film, including the one seen shortly before after Barry leaves the hospital. In this way, the two are visually contrasted and linked as business owners, men with anger issues, and enemies coming together for a conflict.</p>"}],"target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-11745/canvas/1#xywh=275,138,1195,801"},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-11745/canvas/1/f746b87c-f2ca-443a-8ea8-dd403c997579","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2025-08-27T19:49:06.144Z","creator":"Olivia Flores","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>A similar bottle of glass window cleaner can be seen in Barry's apartment. Even these small details suggest that Barry and the Mattress Man are more similar than might seem at a glance.</p>"}],"target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-11745/canvas/1#xywh=1675,720,105,212"}]}]}]}